    • Constructor Detail

      • Cell

        public Cell​(int row,
            int column,
            Maze maze,
            Random rng)
        Cell to be accessed by other classes to generate the mazes.
        Parameters:
        row - Rows are the different columns the maze will use to create the paths.
        column - Columns are the columns to be used for the maze.
        maze - Maze is the complete generation of the attempt.
        rng - Sets up a random number generator to determine the different paths to create.

      • Cell

        public Cell​(EnumSet<Direction> walls,
            int row,
            int column,
            Maze maze,
            Random rng)
        Setting the fields to be used for the maze generation.
        Parameters:
        walls - The parameter walls is the walls of the maze.
        row - Rows to be used to set up how many rows of cells for use in the maze.
        column - Columns to be used to set up how many rows of columns for use in the maze.
        maze - Maze encapsulates all of the fields to create the maze.
        rng - Random number generator to aid in the random generation of paths in the maze.

      • isVisited

        public boolean isVisited()
        This aids the maze generator to know if it should continue destroying walls in the direction it is headed, or return to destroy walls and create a path in a different direction. This will also allow the user to know if they have previously visited a column already.
        Returns:
        isVisited returns true or false.

      • setVisited

        public void setVisited​(boolean visited)
        Sets boolean true if a cell has been visited already.
        Parameters:
        visited - Visited effects the path created and also allows the user to know if they have gone in to a cell previously.

      • getNeighbors
